column5: I refused to spend $30 on a birthday cake so I spent 2.5 hours making one
Nice here's the one I made Kaleb for his first B-day .
yeah when someone makes it them selves it means a lot more
Well done guys !!! .Nothin even comes close to homemade.
You sir  obviously never tried  my first last and only attempt at a B-day cake. The HORROR  Nice looking work in the other posts though
How many decades does each candle represent? 2, 2½ ?
Awesome cake , Dan !!! Your son should be proud of you. Happy birthday to him...enjoy!!

dang........... 2 would be 60...sure ain't there yet 2½...would be dead or 75 whichever comes first  ..................got a long way to go before any of them...but thanks for thinking of me....   do I need some wrinkle cream or something....that was a rhetorical question ..please don't answer it....
Terry.. why is teamemptypockets coming out of your hut.. did your wife visualize the wrong guy while making the cake,,,,
LOL.....it does look like TEP, too funny!  "Until now I thought I was good for nothing," Until now I thought so too Dan. Cheers.....LOL, I guess I owe you a beer for that one.
Great job guys awesome cakes...I made one for a friends 50th couldn't show it on here though or Roy would put me on mod Q...
And here i thought a decade was 10 years!!!!!!! Terry , you were home schooled weren't you?
i tried making bread once...but ended up bricking a house with the final product...  Nice cakes !!!

lets do the math.........I 	will........speak........slowly ...for........some  3 candles.............as...you...said.............2 decades per candle.........each candle 20 years.......X ...that X means times...which means multiply by..(I am keeping it simple)......  2 decades per candle.........each candle 20 years.......X 3 candles.........20 x 3 =60 years..how do you add it up 2.5 decades per candle.......each candle 25 years......X 3 candles.........25 x 3 =75 years  am I missing something.....I did have a late night and was on the road this morning early..but
Did I write 2 or 2½ ?  I meant 1 or 1½!
you had me going  I started second guessing myself............1+1 = 3.....damn new math....
